{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771445045,"nonce":"vxWMHC6aNvMaUqxGeBukoeI1p00=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87sAiGT","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/229","origin":"github"},"title":"Sandboxed agent development: DevContainer with YOLO mode","message":"## Summary\n\nInvestigate using DevContainers as a sandboxed development environment for AI agents, with the goal of enabling **YOLO mode** (no permission prompts) by using container isolation as the security boundary instead of per-command approval.\n\n## Exploration Results\n\nWe tested the existing `.devcontainer/` setup locally with Docker and validated a mount strategy that provides filesystem-enforced isolation.\n\n### What works today\n\n- **Docker image builds** successfully from the existing Dockerfile (~50s)\n- **Full workspace build** inside the container вАФ all 59 packages across 6 layers\n- **Selective mount strategy** provides strong isolation:\n\n| Mount | Mode | Purpose |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `layers/main/*/src/` | **read-only** | Prevents agents from modifying main branch source |\n| `layers/main/*/{build,install,log}` | **anonymous volumes** | Container-local builds, host artifacts untouched |\n| `layers/worktrees/` | **read-write** | Normal worktree workflow preserved |\n| `.agent/` | **read-only** (proposed) | Agents can't modify their own rules |\n| `.agent/scratchpad/` | **read-write** | Temp file workspace |\n\n### Dockerfile gaps\n\nThe current Dockerfile needs:\n1. **`universe` apt repo** вАФ many rosdep dependencies live there\n2. **`rosdep install`** step (or entrypoint) вАФ so the container is build-ready on startup\n3. **`gh` and `jq`** вАФ needed by workflow scripts (`gh_create_issue.sh`, `status_report.sh`, etc.)\n4. **Volume ownership fix** вАФ anonymous volumes start as `root`, need `chown` to `ros` user\n5. **Node.js + Claude Code** вАФ if Claude runs inside the container\n\n### Script compatibility in the container\n\n| Script | Works? | Missing |\n|--------|--------|---------|\n| env.sh | вЬЕ | вАФ |\n| build.sh | вЬЕ | вАФ |\n| set_git_identity_env.sh | вЬЕ | вАФ |\n| worktree_list.sh | вЬЕ | вАФ |\n| worktree_remove.sh | вЬЕ | вАФ |\n| check_branch_updates.sh | вЬЕ | вАФ |\n| worktree_enter.sh | вЬЕ | `gh` (graceful degradation) |\n| worktree_create.sh | вЪ†пЄП | `gh`; also read-only src blocks `git worktree add` |\n| status_report.sh | вЪ†пЄП | `gh`, `jq` (works with `--quick`) |\n| gh_create_issue.sh | вЭМ | `gh`, `jq` |\n\n## Proposed Architecture\n\n**Goal**: Claude Code runs inside the container in YOLO mode. The container filesystem provides the safety boundary.\n\n```\nвФМвФАвФАвФА Container (YOLO mode) вФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР\nвФВ  Claude Code + full tool access, no permission      вФВ\nвФВ  prompts вАФ container IS the sandbox                 вФВ\nвФВ                                                     вФВ\nвФВ  /workspace/                                        вФВ\nвФВ    layers/main/*/src/     вЖТ read-only               вФВ\nвФВ    layers/main/*/{build,install,log} вЖТ volumes      вФВ\nвФВ    layers/worktrees/      вЖТ read-write              вФВ\nвФВ    .agent/                вЖТ read-only               вФВ\nвФВ    .agent/scratchpad/     вЖТ read-write              вФВ\nвФВ                                                     вФВ\nвФВ  Tools: node, claude, gh, git, colcon, rosdep, jq   вФВ\nвФВ  Auth: API key or mounted ~/.claude credentials     вФВ\nвФФвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФШ\n```\n\n### Safety model comparison\n\n| Guardrail | Current (host) | Container |\n|-----------|---------------|-----------|\n| Don't modify main source | Convention (CLAUDE.md) | **Read-only mount** (enforced) |\n| Don't clobber shared builds | Convention | **Anonymous volumes** (enforced) |\n| Don't modify agent rules | Convention | **Read-only mount** (enforced) |\n| Don't push bad code | Permission prompt | Branch protection on GitHub |\n| Agent isolation | Worktrees (shared filesystem) | **Separate containers** |\n\n## Open Questions\n\n### 1. Worktree creation chicken-and-egg\n`git worktree add` writes to `.git/` inside the read-only src mount. Options:\n- Create worktrees on the host before launching the container\n- Mount `.git/` dirs writable, source files read-only (complex)\n- Accept worktree creation happens outside the container\n\n### 2. Claude Code authentication\n- **API key** (`-e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=...`) uses pay-as-you-go billing\n- **Subscription auth** requires mounting `~/.claude/` вАФ needs testing to see if OAuth tokens are portable across environments\n- Investigate: what files in `~/.claude/` carry auth state?\n\n### 3. Credential plumbing\n```\n-v ~/.ssh:/home/ros/.ssh:ro           # git push/pull\n-v ~/.config/gh:/home/ros/.config/gh:ro  # gh CLI\n-v ~/.claude:/home/ros/.claude:ro     # Claude subscription auth (TBD)\n```\n\n### 4. Container lifecycle\n- Pre-built image with all deps for fast startup?\n- One container per task (ephemeral) vs long-lived?\n- Named volumes for build caching across container restarts?\n\n### 5. Launcher script\nThe mount flags are verbose (~20 lines). Need a `docker-run-agent.sh` script that:\n- Auto-discovers layer workspace dirs\n- Generates the mount flags\n- Optionally creates a worktree on the host first\n- Passes credentials\n\n### 6. Git push risk\nYOLO mode + network access means Claude could `git push --force`. GitHub branch protection rules become the last line of defense. Consider whether to restrict network access beyond API endpoints.\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. Fix Dockerfile gaps (universe repo, rosdep, gh, jq, volume ownership)\n2. Test Claude Code auth portability when mounting `~/.claude/`\n3. Build launcher script for the mount strategy\n4. Test full agent workflow: create worktree (host) вЖТ launch container вЖТ build/test/edit вЖТ commit/push\n5. Document the sandboxed workflow\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}